      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hey all. I\u0027ve switched to a less aggressive factoring in the endpoints. Also, I\u0027ve factored out a request/response-serving pattern between my 2 tests. If the latter passes muster with you, I intend for it to be expanded to other tests in the file in a future CL. I think it clarifies the intent at the call sites, and it removes 2 pieces of uninteresting state from each test function.\n\nAlong with whatever else you see, I\u0027m interested in opinions on my passing the server and ResponseRecorder around by value in responseOf(). I went back and forth but finally decided to come down on the side of conveying \"I\u0027m not going to mutate this\" for the server (though we could of course stomp all over the copied switchboard ptr inside it). The by-value return of the ResponseRecorder was a total coin flip. It\u0027s big, so I could see a by-ref in production code, but it\u0027s nice to convey that nobody else is holding onto it (not that one would expect a test helper procedure to). Input welcome. Thanks for the review!",
      "revId": "0b1ac519f8689683aa9dd457c9aca50f2777426c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
